When adding the Confluence Page Gadget into a Confluence page, the page will load fine, but there would be a message at the top of the gadget. Something like:

{noformat}
The resource https://instancename.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/quickreload/latest/undefined?since=<ID>, cannot be found.
{noformat}

While visiting _http://<CONFLUENCE_BASEURL>/aboutconfluencepage.action_
{quote}
 Copyright © 2003 - 2013 Atlassian Corporation Pty Ltd.

The use of this product is subject to the terms of the Atlassian End User Agreement, unless other specified therein.
{quote}

Were it should read:
{quote}
 Copyright © 2003 - 2013 Atlassian Corporation Pty Ltd.

The use of this product is subject to the terms of the Atlassian End User Agreement, unless *otherwise* specified therein.
{quote}

Adding wiki markup for page and space links within the header of the theme for a space does not render correctly in the pages.  For example:

{warning}This documentation space is under construction and subject to change.{warning}
  {tip}This documentation is for the current version of blah. For other versions refer to [insert space name|insert space key:insert page name]{tip}

For pages within this space, the header will show the actual wiki markup code instead of the link to the space and page.

On previous versions of Confluence when you typed a color in the bgcolor macro that color would be set as the background. On the latest version of Confluence the color defaults to green, regardless of what was typed in. 

{quote}
Typing in this will result on a Background Color macro box with no color set. It defaults to green:
{noformat}
{bgcolor:#blue}
{noformat}
{quote}

The workaround is to Edit the macro itself and set the color, then it get's set properly.

h5.steps to reproduce
# grant Confluence access to the maximum number of users in the license tier;
# delete an account without removing its _Can Use_ permission;
# go to *User Management > Application Access* - Confluence licenses will show _-1_;
# attempt to switch to the _Confluence_ tab - an error will be displayed:
{quote}Whoops!
We are currently unable to retrieve your licensing information for this product. Please try reloading the page in a few minutes.{quote}

Attempts to add users to groups with Global Permission to use Confluence will result in an error message stating that the license limit has been reached.

*Workaround:* go to Confluence Global Permissions and revoke the _Can Use_ permission from the deleted account.

